Model Comparison

# allresults: a list with 100 objects, one for each tree
# each object: a list of 9 models run in a tree

# Make a table of AIC values
resaic <- do.call(rbind, lapply(1:100, function(x) unlist(lapply(allresults[[x]], AIC))))

# calculate delta AIC
resdaic <- t(apply(resaic, 1, function(x) x - min(x)))

how many times each model had a deltaAIC lower than 2 across the 100 phylogenies

# Plot AIC results
ggplot(data=plotdat, aes(x=value, fill=model)) + 
    geom_density(alpha=0.4) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept=2), lty=2) + geom_vline(aes(xintercept=4), lty=2, col='grey') +
    theme_bw() + xlab('delta AIC') + scale_fill_discrete(guide = guide_legend(title = "model"))

(black line is delta AIC = 2, grey line is delta AIC = 4)

Model averaged estimates

# put all coefficients and all standard errors in separate data frames
allcoef <- do.call(cbind, lapply(allestimates, "[", "coef"))
allster <- do.call(cbind, lapply(allestimates, "[", "StErr"))^2

# Create new data frame with model-averaged parameters accross trees

modavgres <- data.frame(mean.coef = rowMeans(allcoef, na.rm=T))

modavgres$se.btw.trees <- sqrt(apply(allcoef, 1, var, na.rm=TRUE))
modavgres$se.win.trees <- sqrt(apply(allster, 1, mean, na.rm=TRUE))

modavgres$pooled.ster <- sqrt(
  apply(allcoef, 1, var, na.rm=TRUE)^2 + # variance of the estimates across trees
  apply(allster, 1, mean, na.rm=TRUE)^2 # mean variance of the estimates within trees
  )

modavgres$CIlwr <- modavgres$mean.coef - 1.96* modavgres$pooled.ster
modavgres$CIupr <- modavgres$mean.coef + 1.96* modavgres$pooled.ster

round(modavgres,3)
